<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Seveca</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Lurker<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Oct 2002<br />
	Location: Reno, NV
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Been reading posts on the site recently.  I think this is my first post, so I better make it a good one.<br />
<br />
/startrant<br />
I just think Alchemy needs to be re-tooled, and many others feel the same way from what I have read.  There is no call for any of our potions, with the exception of higher end multiple person raids.  And even then most people don't want potions because of whatever reason.  So what is the point?  I am a 47 Shaman with an alchemy skill of 108 now and the potions I have made to get to this level do not sell, even in the bazaar.  Sure, I can make SoW potions and try to undercut my brethren Shaman to make a couple plat, but that will just drive the prices down to where we make 1pp per 10 dose.  I already see that happening.  On Tribunal Server, it was so bad that I saw 10 Dose SoW potions going for 69p 9g 9s 9c.  How friggin greedy do you have to be???  I stopped trying to sell 'em now, and just give the potions I make to my guildies and friends.  What is the point?!?!?!<br />
<br />
Other tradeskills have recieved upgrades, why not Alchemy?  Seems like blacksmithing gets ten new smithed armors every upgrade that are better than the last.  What do they have against Alchemy?<br />
<br />
My opinion only here, but I have been playing EQ for a year, so I don't know exactly what it was like the first year it came out.  But in talks with old-time-EQ'ers (we all know the ones....I was here for Beta! lol), the weapons and equipment was so far below what it is now that I think our potions would have been HIGHLY sought after.  (I still have a hard time thinking that the Short Sword of Ykesha being the most uber weapon in the game.)  But they have thrown so many different variations of weapons and armor that have stats and proc's that our potions have become useless.  Sometimes even our spells can be useless with the equipment that is out there.   I had a warrior, prolly 40-50 because we were in DL, tell me not to waste mana on him for a strength buff because he was already maxed at 255.<br />
/endrant<br />
<br />
Some things I would like to see is potions that don't have ANY negative stats.  Maybe even ressurection potions, with a set up like the clerics have.  Meaning, first rez potion is no exp, next is minor exp, then more, then more, etc..  Or maybe some Illusion potions.  SOMETHING!!  And the prices!  I know I just about fainted when I saw the prices on some of the higher end reagents.  And they saw Jewelcraft is expensive?<br />
<br />
Ok, ok, ok....so NOW /endrant.<br />
<br />
I was happy that Shaman are the only ones to get Alchemy.  Too bad it is not as useful as it should be.  Or could be, I should say.<br />
<br />
Hopefully there will be some responses to this so my venting won't go unnoticed.<br />
<br />
<br />
Seveca Dabearhugger<br />
Barbarian Shaman of 47 Winters<br />
Tribunal Server<br />
<br />
Raidr<br />
Barbarian Warrior of 42 Bloodlettings<br />
Tribunal Server<br />
<br />
Sevraider Dabushhuger<br />
Wood Elf Druid of 40 Bushes<br />
Tribunal Server</p>
	
	
	
