<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Seveca</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Lurker<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Oct 2002<br />
	Location: Reno, NV
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Garf....sorry if I bored you, but I haven't read all the posts.  Just needed to vent a little.  And BTW, I guess tests would be testic.....nm.<br />
<br />
Andal....I understand your opinion and agree with it to a point.  I am not trying to make 150K by my alchemy.  I would like to be able to make some potions that would be useful to my guildmates and friends that are not going to cause me to go broke.<br />
<br />
As far as making SoW potions go, I am only saying that I made money to work on my Alchemy by selling SoW potions in WC.  Now, with people undercutting each other on EVERYTHING in the bazaar, a young Shaman that wants to increase his/her skill in this area will not be able to make any plat selling SoW potions in the bazaar because some of us only fail once or twice per stack, whereas some with a lower skill level might fail 8 to 10 times.  I always considered myself part of a brotherhood as a Shaman.  A brotherhood who try to help each other.  But, by undercutting each other on prices for the few potions people will pay for, we cut out the lower levels who do not have the skill level we do to make these potions.<br />
<br />
And yes, maybe when Beta came out it was understood that tradeskills were not designed as ways to generate cash, but that is what they are being used for right now.  Lots of things have changed since Beta, and I am not saying that I agree with them.  I am simply stating the ideology of those playing at this time.  I agree that selling at a lower price is everyone's right.  And as far as the ideation of projection is concerned, I would have to say that I disagree.  The standard rate on Tribunal server for a SoW potion has been 100 pp.  Has been for the time I have been playing at least.  And since the bazaar has opened I have seen a fast decline in price so that only Shaman with higher skill levels can turn a profit at all.  Why did it change?  Because Shaman want to sell more potions to make more money.  So it would be greed that motivates those individuals.<br />
<br />
And as far as the person selling at the lowest price being charitable, I disagree with that also.  Most of those people were not so &quot;charitable&quot; when the going rate was 100 pp.  They were selling them for 99pp and still trying to undercut others.  So they were not charitable, just greedy.  Maybe it was only that way on my server.  And that is only my opinion.<br />
<br />
I really do understand your point, but if potions weren't so expensive to make, I probably wouldn't be bitching and complaining right now.  I mean, hell, to get your skill in baking up to in baking to 135 is minimal compared to attempting one potion that is trivial at 90.  And yes, I understand that our potions give better stats than 99% of all baked items, but it is just an example.<br />
<br />
I am truly sorry, but it was a little offensive to me when that warrior told me that he didn't need a STR buff because he was already maxed unbuffed.  I just wish we could get some new potions that would be more helpful.  Seems that a lot of other tradeskills have recieved improvements to keep up with the EQ upgrades, and Alchemy has not been upgraded in relation to the other tradeskills.<br />
<br />
'Course, I ahve had a couple drinks while writing this, so take it with a grain of salt.<br />
<br />
Seveca Dabearhugger<br />
47 Barbarian Shaman<br />
Tribunal Server</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br />Seveca Dabearhugger<br />
Tribunal Server<br />
<br />
Pain is only weakness leaving the body.</div>
	
	
